I2C multiplexer:
A0, A1, A2 - GND
RST - Vcc via pullup resistor
SCL - PB2
SDA - PB3
SCL and SDA both must be connected to Vcc via pullup resistors (2-10K)


I2C sensors (colour, temperature, magnetism):
Connect each set of sensors to the multiplexer outputs:
Module 1: SC0 and SD0
Module 2: SC1 and SD1
Module 3: SC2 and SD2
Module 4: SC3 and SD3
Pullup resistors to Vcc for all SC* and SD*

Magnetism sensors:
CS - Vcc (enable i2c mode)

Moisture sensors:
Module 1: AIN0 (PE3)
Module 2: AIN1 (PE2)
Module 3: AIN2 (PE1)
Module 4: AIN3 (PE0)

Weight amplifier:
CLK - PA6
DATA - PA7
Make sure to calibrate the scaling factor to scale to the appropriate units.
    - Set scale to 1 (defaults to 1 automatically)
    - Call tare() with zero load on sensor
    - Add known weight
    - read_scaled_avg() and divide result by the known weight to obtain the scaling factor
